 <h2>1 &middot; Upload the document</h2>\n  <div class=\"step\">Download <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Talonsturgill/alaskaaicarousels/main/runs/2026-07-14/carousel.pdf\"><b>carousel.pdf</b></a>\n  (2.63 MB, vector text) &rarr; LinkedIn &rarr; start a post &rarr;\n  add a <b>document</b> &rarr; upload the PDF &rarr; title it:\n  <b>The Anchorage Address</b></div>\n\n  <h2>2 &middot; Paste the post copy</h2>\n  <pre class=\"copy\">An Alaska Native-owned firm just won a $24.96M Navy contract for autonomous stealth boats. They will be built in Oregon.\n\nReconCraft is Alaska-incorporated, Anchorage-based, and Native-owned. On July 8 the Navy handed it $24,960,408, sole source, for autonomous low-profile vessels, boats that barely break the surface.\n\nThe Navy did not compete it. It went sole source through the SBA 8(a) program, built to route federal contracts to Native-owned firms. The boats will be welded in Clackamas, Oregon.\n\nSo what is &quot;Alaska&quot; in this boom? An ownership stake and an address, not a shipyard. A real Native win, and most of what Alaska&#x27;s slice looks like now.\n\nSwipe through how one Anchorage-owned, Oregon-built contract splits Alaska&#x27;s paper from its steel.\n\nIf the firm is Native-owned but the boats are built Outside, does the win count as Alaska&#x27;s?\n\n#AlaskaBusiness #DefenseContracting #Autonomy</pre>\n\n  <h2>3 &middot; Post, then paste this as the FIRST comment (within a minute)</h2>\n  <pre class=\"copy\">Sources for Alaska.Ai Carousel No. 7, the ReconCraft autonomous vessel contract.\n\n1. U.S. Department of War, daily contracts for July 8, 2026. The ReconCraft award, $24,960,408, autonomous low-profile vessels, work in Clackamas Oregon, complete November 2028, not competitively procured under FAR 19.805-1(b)(2), Naval Sea Systems Command, contract N00024-26-C-6324. war.gov/News/Contracts/Contract/Article/4538357/contracts-for-july-8-2026/\n\n2. HigherGov awardee profile, ReconCraft LLC. Alaska incorporation, Anchorage headquarters, Native American and tribally owned, SBA 8(a) certified through December 2, 2026. highergov.com/awardee/reconcraft-llc-10114995/\n\n3. ReconCraft LLC company site. Clackamas Oregon facility, vessels up to 120 feet. reconcraft.com\n\n4. Army Recognition, April 24, 2025. ALPV class figures and the narco-submarine design lineage, about 19.75 meters overall, under 0.61 meters of freeboard, 2,000 to 4,627 kg payload, about 2,200 nautical miles. armyrecognition.com\n\n5. DefenseScoop, March 4, 2026. What the military wants next from autonomous low-profile vessels. defensescoop.com\n\nFull storyboard, report card, and the Alaska AI Docket at alaskaaihq.com</pre>\n\n  <h2>The deck</h2>\n  <div class=\"grid\"><div class=\"slide\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt=\"slide 1\"/><div class=\"cap\">01 \u00b7 <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Talonsturgill/alaskaaicarousels/main/runs/2026-07-14/slide-01.png\">full res</a></div></div><div class=\"slide\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt=\"slide 2\"/><div class=\"cap\">02 \u00b7 <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Talonsturgill/alaskaaicarousels/main/runs/2026-07-14/slide-02.png\">full res</a></div></div><div class=\"slide\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt=\"slide 3\"/><div class=\"cap\">03 \u00b7 <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Talonsturgill/alaskaaicarousels/main/runs/2026-07-14/slide-03.png\">full res</a></div></div><div class=\"slide\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt=\"slide 4\"/><div class=\"cap\">04 \u00b7 <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Talonsturgill/alaskaaicarousels/main/runs/2026-07-14/slide-04.png\">full res</a></div></div><div class=\"slide\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt=\"slide 5\"/><div class=\"cap\">05 \u00b7 <a href=\"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Talonsturgill/alaskaaicarousels/main/runs/2026-07-14/slide-05.png\">full res</a></div></div><div class=\"slide\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,